data.name: Salsa Dancing Chelmsford
data.description:
Want to learn Salsa whilst you exercise, energise and socialise? Beginners are welcome, and no partner is required. Just turn up weekly on Tuesdays at Essex’s premier salsa club, Marconi on Beehive Lane. No need to pre-book.
 
Come and join the fun and learn salsa dancing with the most experienced and well known salsa teachers and promoters in Essex.

Salsa Chillout has entertained and taught thousands of Salseros at most of the UK’s largest events, and have also been invited to teach in Ireland, America and Europe alongside some of the best Salsa teachers in the world. Our experiences include entertaining Middle Eastern Royalty, MP’s and Blue Chip companies as well as at private events. UKA qualified and expertly trained by the biggest names in the industry, these 2x Salsa Award Winners have taught most of the other Salsa promoters and teachers in Essex, and are delighted they are now helping to expand the salsa we all love.

We offer a discounted beginners 6-week course, for 1 or 2 people. Quote code POSB61 (£35) for 1 person, or POSB62 (£65) for 2 people.

Not sure what it's all about and want to try before deciding? If it's your first time with us, quote 'Salsa up my life' on your first visit and we'll offer you £4 entry so you can join the beginners class and try it for yourself!
data.attendeeInstructions: Bring your smile :) There is no dress code, just wear clothing you feel comfortable in . For footwear, the most important thing for dance shoes is that they stay firmly on your feet, and the soles aren’t too sticky! We recommend avoiding rubber soles. Women are recommended to wear high heels, but it is not required. If you already have a pair of dance shoes, great! Otherwise any leather soled shoes that will stay on your feet will be perfect! Plimsoles with non-sticky rubber sole are okay too.

The Mini Marathon is the most fun your child will have whilst running 2.62 miles!

Taking place one week after the Virgin London Marathon on Sunday 29th April, the Greenwich & Bexley Community Hospice Mini Marathon is a 2.62 mile sponsored run around Royal Greenwich Park.

Plus Bills Restaurant in Greenwich is very kindly offering 20% off all food to all Mini Marathon participants dinning between Friday 27th to Saturday 5th May. data.name: Yoga for Healthy Lower Backs
data.description:
12 week yoga course for anyone suffering from chronic low back pain. Simple gentle exercises to increase strength, flexibility and help you become more active. The sessions also include relaxation and breathing techniques. 
Participants receive the Yoga for Healthy Lower Backs book, a relaxation CD and handouts so they can practice at home in between weekly classes. Yoga for Healthy Lower Backs was developed in conjunction with Arthritis UK and proved to be effective when tested in a randomised controlled trial. Gentle yoga classes are recommended by NICE as a first line treatment for non-specific back pain.
The class number is kept small to ensure students receive the individual attention they need.
data.attendeeInstructions: All yoga equipment is provided at the sessions, but participants should bring a blanket and pillow. They will need a yoga mat to practice at home.

data.name: Cruz Basketball Academy
data.description:
We are looking to develop a basketball academy in North London for young people from 4 -12 years old. Basketball is a great sport to play because it burns calories, increases balance, coordination and endurance, helps improve concentration and encourages the development of teamwork.

 

Basketball is a great way to ensure your children get the 60 minutes of physical activity a day that they need.

 

Whether it is introducing your child to the electrifying sport of basketball or providing them with more avenues to advance their sporting aspirations, Cruz Basketball Academy is the programme to stimulate their passion in sports.

 

 

Developing their skills at a pace comfortable to them in a fun and exciting environment, the Academy will coach them in fundamental techniques and team tactics. Besides becoming more proficient in basketball, your child will also acquire essential values such as teamwork, honour and resilience during sessions, thus developing a strong character and moral habits from young.

​

We are very proud of our excellent reputation for training players from around the world as we prepare for upcoming events, seasons, or tournament competition. It is with great honour that we help our player to be at their very best through our comprehensive training and team-building program.

 Players will have the chance to train together in a focused environment with demanding on-court offensive and defensive skill training along with intense off-court strength and conditioning training. Our experienced staff will provide our players with a truly unique bonding experience through training and competition, as well as off-court team building activities.

 

Our Training program will include:

On-court positional basketball skill training

Strength and Conditioning; power, speed, agility, flexibility, injury prevention

Athletic testing and body-composition evaluation

Team-building exercises

Team practice times

data.name: Boccia for All
data.description:
We would like you to come and try boccia, it is a fun exciting game similar to Petanque or French Bouls.  
A disability sport that tests muscle control and accuracy. Players propel balls to land close to a target ball. Two sides compete as individuals, pairs or as a team of three over a set number of ends. Each side has six balls (red or blue) each end to try and score points. Points are accumulated over the course of a match to find a winner.

Sounds simple? It is to get started, but the tactics of the sport offer both tension and excitement.

A ball can be rolled, thrown or kicked. If a player is unable to throw or kick the ball, they can use a ramp. If players are unable to release the ball with their hands, they can use assistive devices – head/hand pointer.

organizer.description:
Kazen translates into English as ‘natural result’. This encompasses the spirit we adopt when practicing martial arts. With hard work and dedication, natural results will be accomplished.
Kai translates into English as ‘School’. Therefore, Kazen Kai is the school of natural results.

The Kazen Kai Martial Arts Association was formed in 2001, when Sensei Kidd and his other instructors felt that the time had come for them to leave the Ishinryu Karate Association and to further develop their own style of teaching. In 2002 we opened our first fulltime Martial Arts Centre in Hutton, Brentwood. Since then Kazen Kai has gone from strength to strength with many clubs across Essex, including additional fulltime Martial Arts Centres in Great Baddow, Chelmsford and Harlow as well as additional clubs in Kent and the North East of England.
Kazen Kai is one of the founder members of the English Karate Federation (EKF) which is the National Governing Body.

data.name: Run to the Deep - exclusive sunset 10k in Hyde Park
data.description:
Celebrate World Oceans Day with an early evening ‘sunset’ 10k race event in Hyde Park in London called Run to the Deep.  

The race starts at 18.30hrs (with registration from 17.30) and covers two laps on tarmac.  It is chip-timed, fully marshalled and signed with arrows and kilometre markers.  Facilities include bag drop, water station and a cash bar.

Tickets: https://runtothedeep10krace.eventbrite.co.uk

Run to the Deep is a race with a difference.  You will be able to tune in to our Run to the Deep app, which chronicles a journey from the sea surface to the Marianas Trench, as you cover the 10k distance. 

Explorer Pierre-Yves Cousteau narrates the virtual race, detailing alien creatures, amazing seascapes, and human exploration stories as you ‘descend’ to the ocean floor. As a passionate ocean advocate, Pierre-Yves also covers the issue of marine plastics and implores people to think about the future of our oceans.

data.name: FREE - TASTER SESSION
data.description:
The session is a 45 minute taster session for people of all fitness abilities including people wanting to start getting active again.  It's a free opportunity to try out Nordic Walking to help you understand just how beneficial Nordic Walking can be for your health and wellbeing. 

Unlike trekking or rambling, Nordic Walking poles are planted behind you to help propel you along (you are taught how to do this!).  This engages the upper body and makes you feel lighter on your feet, which has four major advantages.

1. You use 90% of your major muscles so your upper body gets toned as well as your legs and bottom.
2. You can burn 20 - 40% extra calories by using poles which may help with any weight loss goals.
3. It takes the pressure off your knees and joints and is great for back and neck problems.
4.  You can get the most out of even a fairly short walk!

If you enjoy the taster and want to go on to learn all the full technique then you can sign up for a 4 session Learn to Nordic Walk course with a structured teaching programme to enable you to get fully competent and enable you to join in with group walks if you wish.  It's a lot of fun too.
data.attendeeInstructions:
Nordic walking can be done in comfy clothes to suit the weather of the day.  Do wear sunscreen or a hat to protect yourself from the sun or other appropriate items depending on the weather.  We will be outside enjoying green exercise :)

Flexible shoes or trainers are best.  Preferably not open toe sandals but definitely not flip flops.
data.meetingPoint: At the Nordic Walking Stand (Purple bunting and green gazebo) on the Stockbridge Football Field, as part of Trout N' About Festival.

data.name: Battersea Park Bike Hire
data.description:
Bike hire in a public park. 
Open 7 days a week May to end September, then weekends and most school holidays - 10am to 5.30pm (last hire at 4.25pm) (or dusk in winter)

We don't have fixed sessions - just turn up. 
We ask to keep some surety for the duration of your hire - either a driving licence, bank card, passport or freedom pass.

You must be at least 18 years to complete our hire form for yourself and/or your group - bikes available for 3 years and upwards.

Battersea Park has a nice flat circular route of over a kilometer.
data.attendeeInstructions:
Come fed and watered and wearing shoes for cycling - flip-flops are not ideal.

We give free of charge sessions to Wand Card holders. If you're a Wandsworth resident and have a child (to 25yrs) in receipt of DLA, then chances are you are entitled to a Wand Card - contact Wandsworth's Family Services for more info and and application form.

data.description:

Saracens Sport Foundation employ a qualified running coach to deliver these sessions with the support of volunteers. data.name: Yoga for Rising Warriors - Cancer, MS, Fibromyalgia, Elderly
data.description:
This yoga class is attended by a wide range of would be yogis - people who think they are not fit enough for a regular class, women with breast cancer, MS  and other cancer patients, people with Fibromyalgia - everyone is welcome.

You may have been told to try yoga, but what if you are struggling with tiredness, exhaustion, pain, feel depressed, have scars from operations and other challenges? 
There still is a yoga for you. Depending on how you feel on the day, this class incorporates anything from soulful flow to restorative yogic sleep, from laughter to quiet contemplation, from building strength to accepting limitations within. 

Iris Waller, an experienced yoga therapist, runs this class with inclusivity in mind and will keep you safe during your practice. She hopes to instil a joy and love for yoga and movement that will keep you healthy and strong for life, whatever your journey.

Drop-in class £15 (cash only)

To book or for more information, call Iris Waller at 07971562831

data.name: Walking for Health - Havering
data.description:
Walk your Way to Health with Havering’s Health Walks…

We walk 6 days a week and have walks to support all types of walkers.  Walks vary in length from 30 - 90 minutes and are graded from easy to hard.  There are also longer walks run outside of Walking For Health for those looking for an extra challenge.  Walking for Health Qualified Walk Leaders are always there to assist and advise on all walks.

Everyone is welcome and the walks are FREE!

Please see our attached programme for times, dates and meeting points. There is no need to book, just come along on the day you want to join us. We recommend that everyone starts with an ‘easy’ walk.  Please aim to arrive 15 minutes before the start time to allow for registration.

Our walking programme is here to help support you in leading an active lifestyle, whilst discovering more about the many greenspaces in your local area.  These walks are very popular, with an average of 30 -75 walkers on each walk, so are also a good opportunity to socialise with other people who enjoy walking.

We also run a series of shorter walks specifically for those recovering from illness or injury.  For further information and advice, please contact sportsdevelopment@havering.gov.uk or call 01708 431016
